1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:00,801
"While You Were Sleeping"

2
00:00:14,481 --> 00:00:18,434
"Kyomun Securities"

3
00:01:10,873 --> 00:01:11,707
I...

4
00:01:12,534 --> 00:01:13,807
...believe in you.

5
00:01:15,300 --> 00:01:16,343
Because it's me...

6
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,613
...I can believe in you.

7
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:43,897
"Episode 1"

8
00:01:50,133 --> 00:01:51,781
This makes no sense. This makes no sense.

9
00:01:51,866 --> 00:01:53,980
This is impossible.

10
00:02:15,471 --> 00:02:17,214
What is it? Did you dream again?

11
00:02:18,342 --> 00:02:19,506
What is this smell?

12
00:02:20,119 --> 00:02:21,125
Hey. Stop lighting up things like this.

13
00:02:21,215 --> 00:02:22,809
Open up the window and air out this place.

14
00:02:23,267 --> 00:02:24,601
Is this a room for a human being?

15
00:02:24,686 --> 00:02:26,079
This is a pigpen.

16
00:02:26,164 --> 00:02:27,383
"On the road. Nightime. Winter.
I hugged man I've never seen before"

17
00:02:27,472 --> 00:02:29,379
It's impossible!

18
00:02:30,249 --> 00:02:32,400
What's impossible?
Look at this if you have eyes.

19
00:02:32,501 --> 00:02:33,916
This is a pigpen.

20
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:37,029
This is why I can't eat pork.
Because it smells like you.

21
00:02:37,114 --> 00:02:38,257
That's not it.

22
00:02:38,342 --> 00:02:40,167
I hugged a man I just met in my dreams.

23
00:02:40,252 --> 00:02:41,583
And I'm the one who hugged him first.

24
00:02:41,668 --> 00:02:42,501
You know, don't you?

25
00:02:42,601 --> 00:02:44,357
I'm not the type to hit on a man first.

26
00:02:44,442 --> 00:02:45,583
Of course I do.

27
00:02:45,667 --> 00:02:47,216
How would you hit on
a man looking like that?

28
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:49,801
If you have a conscience at least...

29
00:02:49,901 --> 00:02:50,786
Mother.

30
00:02:50,871 --> 00:02:51,915
Are you sure you're my mother?

31
00:02:52,005 --> 00:02:54,339
Can you please toll the bell for your mom?

32
00:02:54,432 --> 00:02:55,712
Ernest Hemingway.

33
00:03:06,223 --> 00:03:07,625
What does he look like?

34
00:03:07,710 --> 00:03:08,822
Was he handsome?

35
00:03:09,734 --> 00:03:11,416
What can I do about it if he's handsome?

36
00:03:11,501 --> 00:03:12,617
I have a boyfriend.

37
00:03:12,701 --> 00:03:14,483
You went on a blind date once and
went out with him just twice...

38
00:03:14,567 --> 00:03:15,604
...but he's your boyfriend already?

39
00:03:15,689 --> 00:03:17,435
You might marry him if you
go out with him three times.

40
00:03:17,534 --> 00:03:19,201
I hate two timers...

41
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:20,650
...so don't talk
about the man in my dream.

42
00:03:20,734 --> 00:03:21,568
Never.

43
00:03:21,667 --> 00:03:23,803
He'll come into your life
even if you don't want him to.

44
00:03:23,934 --> 00:03:27,089
Your dream always comes true.

45
00:03:27,174 --> 00:03:28,575
I said it's not like that.

46
00:03:34,567 --> 00:03:35,680
I heard that someone is moving
in across from our house.

47
00:03:35,776 --> 00:03:37,001
I guess they're moving in today.

48
00:03:38,334 --> 00:03:40,222
Handsome brothers.

49
00:03:41,067 --> 00:03:42,601
Are they brothers?

50
00:03:43,029 --> 00:03:44,449
Take this over to them.

51
00:03:44,534 --> 00:03:46,149
Who brings people rice cakes just
because they move in these days?

52
00:03:46,234 --> 00:03:46,777
It's old fashioned.

53
00:03:46,862 --> 00:03:49,536
It's not old fashioned.
It's being kind.

54
00:03:51,365 --> 00:03:52,215
Hurry up and go.

55
00:03:59,327 --> 00:04:00,367
It's that man.

56
00:04:00,701 --> 00:04:02,518
The man that I hugged in my dream.

57
00:04:02,603 --> 00:04:03,307
What?

58
00:04:12,517 --> 00:04:14,350
Hello. I just moved across the street.

59
00:04:14,434 --> 00:04:15,113
Please leave.

60
00:04:15,198 --> 00:04:17,159
And please stop coming to our
house like this in the future.

61
00:04:17,244 --> 00:04:19,334
We refuse any greetings or kindnesses.

62
00:04:19,434 --> 00:04:20,495
I'm sorry.

63
00:04:23,923 --> 00:04:26,016
Jeez. What in the world?

64
00:04:27,634 --> 00:04:29,435
Hey. I told you that people
don't accept rice cakes.

65
00:04:29,534 --> 00:04:31,243
You didn't smile, did you?

66
00:04:31,328 --> 00:04:32,067
I smiled. I smiled.

67
00:04:32,172 --> 00:04:34,338
I smiled like a fool.

68
00:04:35,258 --> 00:04:36,068
Really?

69
00:04:37,267 --> 00:04:39,279
It's not easy to be that rude.

70
00:04:39,534 --> 00:04:40,101
Was it a woman?

71
00:04:40,179 --> 00:04:40,783
Yes.

72
00:04:40,931 --> 00:04:43,683
You should date her.
I think she's perfect for you.

73
00:04:50,067 --> 00:04:50,968
Hey.

74
00:04:58,481 --> 00:05:01,563
Mom. You should've told me
if you were going to use the car.

75
00:05:01,648 --> 00:05:03,166
I'm going to be late if I take the bus.

76
00:05:08,341 --> 00:05:09,674
Mom. Mom.

77
00:05:10,334 --> 00:05:11,678
It's that man. It's that man.

78
00:05:12,268 --> 00:05:14,300
The man from my dream.

79
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:17,065
Miss. Could you please move over?

80
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:18,934
-I can't fall for him.
-Okay?

81
00:05:19,033 --> 00:05:20,066
Hang up for now.

82
00:05:22,961 --> 00:05:24,039
Let's calm down.

83
00:05:24,601 --> 00:05:26,500
I'm not interested in him at all.

84
00:05:26,585 --> 00:05:27,760
Not at all.

85
00:05:32,868 --> 00:05:34,033
Why is he sitting next to me?

86
00:05:34,601 --> 00:05:36,356
There are three spaces to my left
and four spaces to my right...

87
00:05:36,441 --> 00:05:38,501
Why is he sitting next to me
when there are a lot of spaces?

88
00:05:40,167 --> 00:05:41,701
Is he hitting on me?

89
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:42,983
No.

90
00:05:43,067 --> 00:05:45,234
Don't jump to conclusions.
I can't embarrass myself.

91
00:05:48,851 --> 00:05:49,782
He's coming closer to me.

92
00:05:50,772 --> 00:05:53,039
I'm not jumping to conclusions
or embarrassing myself.

93
00:05:55,934 --> 00:05:57,223
He's coming closer to me again.

94
00:05:57,751 --> 00:06:00,962
If I'm careless, I'll become a woman
that he knows from being his neighbor.

95
00:06:01,047 --> 00:06:03,066
Then I'll become his lover
from a woman that he knows.

96
00:06:03,167 --> 00:06:05,170
-I'm not interested in you.
-There's space for you to seat now.

97
00:06:09,067 --> 00:06:10,403
What are you talking about?

98
00:06:11,167 --> 00:06:12,216
What in the world?

99
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:15,642
-She thinks that he's hitting on her.
-My gosh!

100
00:06:21,184 --> 00:06:22,850
Miss. You should ride
the bus across the street.

101
00:06:22,934 --> 00:06:24,283
The next stop is the final stop.

102
00:06:24,367 --> 00:06:25,168
I know that.

103
00:06:25,267 --> 00:06:27,144
Why can't I get on
the bus before the final stop?

104
00:06:30,175 --> 00:06:33,301
-What in the world?
-So embarrassing.

105
00:06:38,167 --> 00:06:40,267
We refuse any greetings or kindnesses.

106
00:06:40,367 --> 00:06:41,467
I'm sorry.

107
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:44,978
That woman's voice...

108
00:06:48,130 --> 00:06:52,834
That is the voice from the intercom.
That rude woman...

109
00:06:52,934 --> 00:06:53,945
Jeez!

110
00:06:54,408 --> 00:06:55,658
It's okay. It's okay.

111
00:06:55,743 --> 00:06:57,750
This isn't embarrassing at all.

112
00:06:59,300 --> 00:07:00,338
You did well.

113
00:07:01,144 --> 00:07:02,318
I told him first.

114
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:06,168
Mom. I think that dream
is going to come true.

115
00:07:06,267 --> 00:07:08,235
Did you fall for that man already?

116
00:07:08,334 --> 00:07:09,717
Is the door of your
heart an automatic door?

117
00:07:09,801 --> 00:07:12,068
How does it open even
before it's knocked on?

118
00:07:12,167 --> 00:07:13,195
It just opens wide.

119
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:15,784
No. He's attracted to me.

120
00:07:15,868 --> 00:07:16,871
How do you know?

121
00:07:16,956 --> 00:07:19,739
Why did he sit so close to me?

122
00:07:20,067 --> 00:07:22,334
You said he did that
to make space for the girls?

123
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:24,535
He's a total pro.

124
00:07:24,634 --> 00:07:26,568
Gosh. He's quite skilled.

125
00:07:26,667 --> 00:07:29,651
From what I can see,
you're clueless when it comes to men.

126
00:07:32,782 --> 00:07:33,750
Let me pay the bill.

127
00:07:35,300 --> 00:07:36,926
One order of pork belly and kimchi stew.

128
00:07:37,011 --> 00:07:38,116
It's 17,000 won.

129
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:39,028
Okay.

130
00:07:43,052 --> 00:07:45,031
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

131
00:07:51,801 --> 00:07:54,001
-Thank you.
-Yes. I enjoyed the meal.

132
00:07:58,647 --> 00:07:59,379
What's wrong?

133
00:07:59,934 --> 00:08:00,933
Do you know him?

134
00:08:01,501 --> 00:08:03,358
I had a dream about three months ago.

135
00:08:04,100 --> 00:08:07,253
That man with the band aid on his hand...

136
00:08:08,219 --> 00:08:09,568
He tried to smoke hen it was snowing.

137
00:08:09,715 --> 00:08:13,071
But he caught fire as soon as
he uses his lighter.

138
00:08:13,601 --> 00:08:15,182
When?
Where?

139
00:08:15,267 --> 00:08:16,434
I don't know that.

140
00:08:16,534 --> 00:08:18,650
The hand with that
band aid used the lighter.

141
00:08:18,734 --> 00:08:20,943
Then it will happen soon. My gosh!

142
00:08:22,247 --> 00:08:23,274
Mister.

143
00:08:27,100 --> 00:08:28,025
Mister.

144
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:29,925
Let me have
your cigarettes and lighter.

145
00:08:30,010 --> 00:08:30,559
Why?

146
00:08:30,644 --> 00:08:32,573
Smoking is bad for you.
It causes cancer.

147
00:08:32,658 --> 00:08:36,093
If I smoke or not,
what does that have to do with you?

148
00:08:36,178 --> 00:08:37,115
Move away.

149
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:39,110
Mister. You'll die if you smoke.

150
00:08:39,195 --> 00:08:41,347
Are you women crazy?

151
00:08:41,432 --> 00:08:43,623
Move away. I said move.

152
00:08:48,847 --> 00:08:50,181
Listen to me!

153
00:08:50,266 --> 00:08:52,268
I told you that you'll die if you smoke.

154
00:08:52,367 --> 00:08:53,768
Just let me fool you and listen to me.

155
00:08:53,853 --> 00:08:55,666
What bad luck I have...

156
00:09:05,167 --> 00:09:07,143
Hey. I took this away from him.
Will this be enough?

157
00:09:08,567 --> 00:09:10,483
Forget it. It's no use.

158
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:13,134
That was his choice.
It's his fate.

159
00:09:13,234 --> 00:09:14,104
How can you say that?

160
00:09:14,189 --> 00:09:15,613
If we know that,
we should try to change it.

161
00:09:30,402 --> 00:09:31,555
We can't change it.

162
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,978
Who would believe me?

163
00:09:42,501 --> 00:09:44,801
How can I tell him that
I saw him in my dream?

164
00:09:45,234 --> 00:09:46,735
Where did that lighter go?

165
00:09:46,820 --> 00:09:49,122
But my dream always comes true.

166
00:09:50,067 --> 00:09:51,324
If you want to live...

167
00:09:52,225 --> 00:09:53,900
...you must listen to
what I'm saying no matter what.

168
00:09:57,611 --> 00:09:59,565
Who would believe such crazy words?

169
00:10:01,634 --> 00:10:03,903
Father didn't believe it either and died.

170
00:10:07,706 --> 00:10:09,876
We can't change fate.

171
00:10:11,421 --> 00:10:13,144
We can't change it
just because we know it.

172
00:10:38,434 --> 00:10:44,434
"While You Were Sleeping"

173
00:10:47,372 --> 00:10:48,916
I'll have this cake.

174
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,732
And please include
as many candles as possible.

175
00:10:51,817 --> 00:10:52,867
Whose birthday is it?

176
00:10:53,375 --> 00:10:56,001
Today is Prosecutor Jung's
first day at work.

177
00:10:56,100 --> 00:10:57,209
So, we should celebrate.

178
00:10:57,294 --> 00:10:58,835
Why do we have to celebrate
out of the blue?

179
00:10:58,920 --> 00:11:00,126
Look at this.

180
00:11:00,211 --> 00:11:01,517
We should celebrate.

181
00:11:01,601 --> 00:11:02,435
Let's celebrate.

182
00:11:02,534 --> 00:11:04,201
We should make it a national holiday.

183
00:11:04,300 --> 00:11:05,617
He looks smart.

184
00:11:05,701 --> 00:11:06,502
Don't you think so?

185
00:11:06,601 --> 00:11:09,135
Prosecutor Jung looks really smart,
doesn't he?

186
00:11:09,507 --> 00:11:10,968
I really like him.

187
00:11:12,634 --> 00:11:13,765
Look at him.

188
00:11:13,850 --> 00:11:15,906
I'm so disappointed in you, Hyangmi.

189
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,578
When you used to work with me,
you used to say that about me?

190
00:11:18,834 --> 00:11:20,895
Are you already saying that about
Prosecutor Jung instead of me?

191
00:11:20,980 --> 00:11:22,543
Oh my gosh, Prosecutor Lee...

192
00:11:23,439 --> 00:11:24,686
No, Attorney Lee.

193
00:11:25,210 --> 00:11:26,434
I'll pay for everything.

194
00:11:26,534 --> 00:11:27,550
That's okay.

195
00:11:27,634 --> 00:11:28,734
You don't need to do that.

196
00:11:28,834 --> 00:11:29,692
That's okay.

197
00:11:29,801 --> 00:11:31,901
Its Prosecutor Jung's first day at work.

198
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:32,934
I should congratulate him too.

199
00:11:33,033 --> 00:11:34,528
Do you know our
Prosecutor Jung Jaechan?

200
00:11:34,613 --> 00:11:35,495
Of course.

201
00:11:35,701 --> 00:11:38,335
I was his tutor long time ago.

202
00:11:39,100 --> 00:11:41,750
Prosecutor Jung doesn't
look like he'd be tutored.

203
00:11:41,834 --> 00:11:43,001
What are you talking about?

204
00:11:43,100 --> 00:11:44,500
He was the last in his whole school
all the time.

205
00:11:44,601 --> 00:11:45,316
Really?

206
00:11:45,400 --> 00:11:46,367
Really?

207
00:11:46,598 --> 00:11:47,807
That's unexpected.

208
00:11:49,273 --> 00:11:50,893
Okay. What does this mean?

209
00:11:50,978 --> 00:11:51,450
Read it.

210
00:11:51,534 --> 00:11:53,075
"13 years ago."

211
00:11:53,160 --> 00:11:55,213
This is so easy.

212
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:58,767
"Just" means right now
and "ice" means ice.

213
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:00,961
If you put them together, "just ice".

214
00:12:01,046 --> 00:12:02,935
Freeze right now.

215
00:12:04,518 --> 00:12:05,667
No way.

216
00:12:05,767 --> 00:12:07,583
He was that stupid.

217
00:12:07,667 --> 00:12:10,700
No. If he's an idiot prosecutor,
you'll have a hard time.

218
00:12:11,393 --> 00:12:12,623
No way.

219
00:12:12,708 --> 00:12:15,730
He's still a prosecutor,
so he can't be that stupid.

220
00:12:25,265 --> 00:12:26,448
I hate that.

221
00:12:27,569 --> 00:12:28,628
Hey. Prosecutor Jung.

222
00:12:34,230 --> 00:12:35,187
Yoobum?

223
00:12:39,398 --> 00:12:40,367
Was it two years ago?

224
00:12:40,775 --> 00:12:41,846
When I first started
working as a prosecutor...

225
00:12:41,931 --> 00:12:44,049
...I received an award from
the Director of Prosecutor General...

226
00:12:44,133 --> 00:12:46,165
...for my work on Hamba case
and serial murder case.

227
00:12:46,395 --> 00:12:50,016
I just put my spoon on
the table you prepared...

228
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:51,258
...but I received an award for it.

229
00:12:51,343 --> 00:12:52,705
Oh my gosh. That's not true.

230
00:12:53,665 --> 00:12:56,401
I'm Investigator Choi Damdong.

231
00:12:56,501 --> 00:12:57,926
Yes. It's nice to meet you.
I'm Jung Jaechan.

232
00:12:58,011 --> 00:12:58,667
And this is...

233
00:12:58,767 --> 00:13:00,913
I'm Assistant Moon Hyangmi.

234
00:13:01,222 --> 00:13:02,582
Yes. It's nice to meet you.

235
00:13:09,783 --> 00:13:10,614
What are you doing here, Yoobum?

236
00:13:10,699 --> 00:13:11,501
What do you mean?

237
00:13:11,601 --> 00:13:15,181
You returned home in glory,
so I should come and congratulate you.

238
00:13:15,304 --> 00:13:17,568
Then the two of you met
as a tutor and student.

239
00:13:17,667 --> 00:13:20,116
But now you're meeting again
as a prosecutor and a lawyer.

240
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,106
Is that right?

241
00:13:21,625 --> 00:13:22,852
I just came to say hello.

242
00:13:22,937 --> 00:13:24,369
I thought we can help each other a lot.

243
00:13:24,454 --> 00:13:25,345
Do you remember?

244
00:13:25,831 --> 00:13:26,668
Win-win?

245
00:13:28,634 --> 00:13:29,568
Just a moment.

246
00:13:30,534 --> 00:13:32,248
Yes. Did you get my text?

247
00:13:32,580 --> 00:13:34,614
I want you to make some time on the 14th.

248
00:13:35,354 --> 00:13:37,383
What do you mean why?
It's Valentine's Day.

249
00:13:38,512 --> 00:13:41,068
Remember the restaurant that
you wanted to go to?

250
00:13:41,298 --> 00:13:42,315
I actually know the place.

251
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:44,867
Jaechan. Do you know
what win-win means?

252
00:13:49,098 --> 00:13:49,869
Win-win?

253
00:13:50,385 --> 00:13:51,493
Is it Chinese?

254
00:13:52,968 --> 00:13:53,941
What that means is...

255
00:13:54,026 --> 00:13:57,103
Your father told me that
he'll raise my tutor fee...

256
00:13:57,303 --> 00:13:59,417
...10,000 won every time you
go up one place at your school.

257
00:13:59,501 --> 00:14:00,926
You should forget about that money.

258
00:14:01,171 --> 00:14:03,275
I can't go up no matter what.

259
00:14:06,411 --> 00:14:08,288
We can just fabricate your report card.

260
00:14:10,465 --> 00:14:11,550
What...

261
00:14:11,667 --> 00:14:13,374
My father is a police officer.

262
00:14:13,459 --> 00:14:14,320
If we get caught...

263
00:14:14,888 --> 00:14:16,517
...he'll put both of us in jail.

264
00:14:16,601 --> 00:14:18,491
We just have to raise it slowly
without letting him catch on.

265
00:14:18,785 --> 00:14:21,611
Hey. If you go up 30 places,
I'll earn 300,000 won.

266
00:14:21,813 --> 00:14:22,962
I'll give you half.

267
00:14:24,326 --> 00:14:26,372
You said you wanted to buy a motorcycle.

268
00:14:26,457 --> 00:14:28,578
When are you going to
buy it with your allowances?

269
00:14:29,747 --> 00:14:30,858
It's good for me since I'll make money...

270
00:14:30,943 --> 00:14:32,506
...and it's good for you since
you'll be able to buy your motorcycle.

271
00:14:34,474 --> 00:14:36,435
Your father will be happy
since your grades are going up.

272
00:14:36,551 --> 00:14:38,420
This is good for everyone.

273
00:14:38,767 --> 00:14:40,413
That's what is called win-win.

274
00:14:44,273 --> 00:14:46,181
So you have to come no matter what.
Do you understand?

275
00:14:46,801 --> 00:14:47,520
Okay.

276
00:14:48,367 --> 00:14:48,954
Hey.

277
00:14:49,434 --> 00:14:50,884
Make some time soon.

278
00:14:50,968 --> 00:14:52,769
I'll take you to a great sushi place.

279
00:14:52,868 --> 00:14:53,535
I'm going.

280
00:14:53,839 --> 00:14:54,501
Bye.

281
00:14:54,613 --> 00:14:57,788
-Bye.
-Bye.

282
00:15:25,886 --> 00:15:26,959
So...

283
00:15:28,234 --> 00:15:29,530
In the end...

284
00:15:29,714 --> 00:15:31,551
...mom died because of me.

285
00:15:32,062 --> 00:15:33,320
Because of...

286
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:36,795
...the accident that I caused.

287
00:15:37,214 --> 00:15:38,629
Hongjoo...

288
00:15:39,987 --> 00:15:42,875
Please tell me that it's just a dream.

289
00:15:47,323 --> 00:15:49,154
Wake me up please.

290
00:15:49,239 --> 00:15:50,950
Come to your senses.

291
00:16:14,763 --> 00:16:16,142
What do I do?

292
00:16:26,534 --> 00:16:32,168
"Aunt. Long hair. Mom's will..."

293
00:16:33,767 --> 00:16:39,701
"Because of the accident
that I caused..."

294
00:16:52,968 --> 00:16:53,908
Hongjoo.

295
00:16:53,993 --> 00:16:55,247
Eat and wash up.

296
00:16:57,014 --> 00:16:57,631
Hey.

297
00:16:57,801 --> 00:16:59,489
Your eyes. Why are they so puffy?

298
00:16:59,574 --> 00:17:00,461
Did you cry?

299
00:17:01,067 --> 00:17:02,629
No. It's because I ate ramyeon
last night before I went to bed.

300
00:17:02,714 --> 00:17:03,963
I'm going to wash up first.

301
00:17:04,477 --> 00:17:05,991
Eat before you wash up.

302
00:17:06,890 --> 00:17:09,094
A big explosion occurred.

303
00:17:09,634 --> 00:17:11,756
Self-service gas station in Osun-dong.

304
00:17:11,841 --> 00:17:15,367
A man who got out of a SUV
put a cigarette in his mouth.

305
00:17:15,452 --> 00:17:19,367
With the gas pump in his hand
he approaches the gas tank.

306
00:17:19,452 --> 00:17:21,034
And the moment he lit his lighter...

307
00:17:21,138 --> 00:17:23,639
...the fire started from the oil
mist from the gas tank.

308
00:17:23,734 --> 00:17:26,401
The gas station is engulfed immediately.

309
00:17:26,501 --> 00:17:29,805
Due to the accident,
37 year old Mr. Kim died at the scene...

310
00:17:29,890 --> 00:17:32,517
That's the man from the last time, right?

311
00:17:32,601 --> 00:17:34,486
The man that you told not to smoke...
Isn't he?

312
00:17:40,042 --> 00:17:40,826
Hongjoo!

313
00:17:43,103 --> 00:17:44,052
Hongjoo.

314
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:46,465
Let go.
Let go.

315
00:17:46,911 --> 00:17:48,133
Let go.

316
00:17:48,265 --> 00:17:49,710
What's wrong with you?

317
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:54,850
It happened to him exactly like my dream.

318
00:17:55,040 --> 00:17:58,310
I know, but there was
nothing we could do.

319
00:17:58,677 --> 00:18:00,734
It won't change.

320
00:18:01,734 --> 00:18:04,383
Mom. What do I do? Mom...

321
00:18:04,834 --> 00:18:09,448
Mom. What do I do? Mom.

322
00:18:10,485 --> 00:18:11,455
Hongjoo.

323
00:18:11,540 --> 00:18:14,047
Mom.

324
00:18:17,025 --> 00:18:19,932
I'm going to die because
of the accident you caused?

325
00:18:22,910 --> 00:18:24,401
And you don't know
when it's going to happen?

326
00:18:30,633 --> 00:18:33,067
We'll have to put a flower here.

327
00:18:35,577 --> 00:18:37,099
-My gosh.
-You're laughing?

328
00:18:37,662 --> 00:18:39,302
Is this situation funny to you, Mom?

329
00:18:39,387 --> 00:18:41,938
You saw that my dream came true
about that smoking man, didn't you?

330
00:18:42,023 --> 00:18:44,610
My dream has never changed once.

331
00:18:44,695 --> 00:18:47,028
Is that why you cut off
your hair like this?

332
00:18:47,113 --> 00:18:49,358
Did you think that your dream will
change if you change your hair?

333
00:18:49,495 --> 00:18:51,468
I'm not going to grow
my hair from now on.

334
00:18:52,067 --> 00:18:53,834
I had a long hair in my dream.

335
00:18:54,455 --> 00:18:56,068
I didn't know...

336
00:18:56,367 --> 00:18:59,751
My daughter looked
pretty because of her hair.

337
00:19:00,384 --> 00:19:01,492
Mom!

338
00:19:03,208 --> 00:19:05,823
My goodness. Don't worry.

339
00:19:06,241 --> 00:19:08,640
I won't die in vain like that.

340
00:19:09,033 --> 00:19:11,016
You're the only one I have in this world.

341
00:19:11,968 --> 00:19:14,105
So, don't leave me alone.

342
00:19:15,367 --> 00:19:16,388
Okay?

343
00:19:18,422 --> 00:19:20,025
My baby...

344
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,765
I think it's best to put
a flower in your hair.

345
00:19:25,850 --> 00:19:27,032
Mom.

346
00:20:21,901 --> 00:20:23,222
Here's your flower.

347
00:20:27,890 --> 00:20:28,961
Thank you.

348
00:20:29,046 --> 00:20:36,502
"February 14th, 2016."

349
00:20:41,470 --> 00:20:42,304
What are you doing?

350
00:20:45,035 --> 00:20:46,478
Hey. Are you on a date?

351
00:20:46,723 --> 00:20:47,624
Yoobum.

352
00:20:48,057 --> 00:20:50,099
Wow. Did you buy a car too?

353
00:20:51,767 --> 00:20:52,488
What are you doing here?

354
00:20:52,573 --> 00:20:53,860
I'm on a date.

355
00:20:53,945 --> 00:20:55,133
-What about you?
-Well...

356
00:20:55,710 --> 00:20:56,834
Well. Me too.

357
00:20:56,934 --> 00:20:57,662
Yoobum.

358
00:20:57,747 --> 00:20:58,850
Yes. You're here.

359
00:20:59,559 --> 00:21:00,813
You cut your hair.

360
00:21:03,723 --> 00:21:04,506
Oh?

361
00:21:04,832 --> 00:21:05,466
Oh!

362
00:21:06,980 --> 00:21:07,581
What?

363
00:21:08,064 --> 00:21:09,322
Do you two know each other?

364
00:21:09,919 --> 00:21:11,336
Well...

365
00:21:15,646 --> 00:21:17,743
But how do you know him, Yoobum?

366
00:21:17,987 --> 00:21:20,146
Wait. The two of you are dating?

367
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:21,154
Yes.

368
00:21:21,701 --> 00:21:23,162
We're dating, right?

369
00:21:23,247 --> 00:21:23,842
Excuse me?

370
00:21:25,225 --> 00:21:25,858
Yes.

371
00:21:26,377 --> 00:21:28,624
Hey. Do you and your girlfriend
want to join us?

372
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:30,234
-No.
-We can't.

373
00:21:31,397 --> 00:21:32,219
It's fine if you don't want to.

374
00:21:32,304 --> 00:21:33,750
It's cold. Let's go.

375
00:21:33,834 --> 00:21:34,817
Yes. You should go.

376
00:21:34,901 --> 00:21:35,467
Go.

377
00:21:35,552 --> 00:21:36,462
We'll go first.

378
00:21:36,667 --> 00:21:40,132
Jaechan, you even got a car.
You're all grown up.

379
00:21:40,769 --> 00:21:41,576
We're going to go first.

380
00:21:43,462 --> 00:21:44,851
Was it when he was in junior high school?

381
00:21:44,936 --> 00:21:46,572
I bought him a motorcycle.

382
00:21:47,197 --> 00:21:49,130
I think it's been over 10 years ago.

383
00:21:49,237 --> 00:21:50,709
Jaechan is all grown up.

384
00:21:53,369 --> 00:21:55,947
Didn't you steal that motorcycle?

385
00:21:56,683 --> 00:21:59,060
No. I bought it with my money.

386
00:21:59,501 --> 00:22:02,701
I didn't give you enough allowance
for you to buy a motorcycle.

387
00:22:02,801 --> 00:22:04,402
"Winter 2003."

388
00:22:04,486 --> 00:22:05,777
I earned it.

389
00:22:05,889 --> 00:22:06,648
You earned it?

390
00:22:07,194 --> 00:22:08,850
From where? How?

391
00:22:08,934 --> 00:22:09,624
Sir.

392
00:22:10,025 --> 00:22:11,036
We'll question him.

393
00:22:11,121 --> 00:22:12,536
Why can't you answer me?

394
00:22:14,033 --> 00:22:14,956
Did you steal it?

395
00:22:15,041 --> 00:22:17,269
No. My report card...

396
00:22:18,901 --> 00:22:19,934
Report card?

397
00:22:28,234 --> 00:22:29,883
We fabricated my report card.

398
00:22:30,434 --> 00:22:33,318
Yoobum said that he'd get more
pay for tutoring me if we do that.

399
00:22:34,033 --> 00:22:35,336
We split that in half.

400
00:22:36,667 --> 00:22:40,463
Gosh. Why did you lie about that?

401
00:22:40,919 --> 00:22:44,148
Your father was so proud of
you for getting good grades.

402
00:22:44,835 --> 00:22:46,672
Just say that you're sorry.

403
00:22:46,890 --> 00:22:48,967
But father... The accident was...

404
00:22:53,267 --> 00:22:55,240
-Chief.
-Chief...

405
00:23:32,205 --> 00:23:33,285
Is something wrong?

406
00:23:33,660 --> 00:23:35,409
You keep looking at
your phone since earlier.

407
00:23:35,524 --> 00:23:38,483
I think I have to go home early today.

408
00:23:38,901 --> 00:23:40,736
My mom isn't answering my texts.

409
00:23:40,821 --> 00:23:42,951
Is your mother not feeling well?

410
00:23:43,036 --> 00:23:44,747
It's not like that.

411
00:23:45,467 --> 00:23:47,141
But something doesn't feel right.

412
00:23:50,676 --> 00:23:53,130
I blew out the candle.

413
00:23:53,885 --> 00:23:56,731
And turned off the stove.

414
00:23:59,580 --> 00:24:00,539
The door...

415
00:24:03,911 --> 00:24:05,313
I didn't lock the door.

416
00:24:05,398 --> 00:24:05,944
Excuse me?

417
00:24:07,193 --> 00:24:09,848
I forgot to lock the door.
I have to go home.

418
00:24:12,233 --> 00:24:13,056
Hongjoo.

419
00:24:20,335 --> 00:24:22,967
Mom. Answer the phone.

420
00:24:24,951 --> 00:24:26,098
Just a moment, Hongjoo.

421
00:24:26,229 --> 00:24:27,500
Have you driven on the snow before?

422
00:24:27,601 --> 00:24:29,201
No, I haven't.

423
00:24:29,973 --> 00:24:31,100
What do I do?

424
00:24:31,205 --> 00:24:32,338
Should I take a taxi?

425
00:24:33,316 --> 00:24:34,983
Can I get a taxi right now?

426
00:24:36,440 --> 00:24:38,417
Let me have your key. I'll drive.

427
00:24:39,616 --> 00:24:40,300
But...

428
00:24:40,385 --> 00:24:41,826
I drove on a road like this many times.

429
00:24:41,911 --> 00:24:43,069
Let me have it. I'll drive.

430
00:25:19,149 --> 00:25:19,916
Excuse me.

431
00:25:32,216 --> 00:25:33,499
Why isn't she answering the phone?

432
00:25:33,584 --> 00:25:35,085
Should I call the police?

433
00:25:37,249 --> 00:25:38,537
I'm sure everything is fine.

434
00:25:39,616 --> 00:25:40,445
Hello.

435
00:25:40,821 --> 00:25:41,556
Mom?

436
00:25:42,850 --> 00:25:44,976
Why did you call me so many times?

437
00:25:48,182 --> 00:25:52,031
No. I left my phone at a cafe by accident.

438
00:25:52,116 --> 00:25:53,716
That's why I couldn't answer the phone.

439
00:25:55,658 --> 00:25:57,108
You fool.

440
00:25:57,563 --> 00:25:59,391
I answered it because I found it.

441
00:25:59,749 --> 00:26:01,840
A nice young man found it for me.

442
00:26:01,925 --> 00:26:03,285
Don't lose your cell phone.

443
00:26:03,370 --> 00:26:05,472
Answer the phone right away if I call you.

444
00:26:06,986 --> 00:26:08,300
I'll be home soon.

445
00:26:11,749 --> 00:26:13,532
I'm relieved.

446
00:26:13,616 --> 00:26:15,783
Have you always been close to your mother?

447
00:26:17,216 --> 00:26:18,029
No.

448
00:26:22,954 --> 00:26:23,949
Yoobum.

449
00:26:27,412 --> 00:26:28,378
If...

450
00:26:29,999 --> 00:26:32,405
If I get into an accident...

451
00:26:34,078 --> 00:26:35,916
...will you protect my mom?

452
00:26:36,015 --> 00:26:38,063
What are you talking about? What accident?

453
00:26:38,371 --> 00:26:39,257
No.

454
00:26:39,526 --> 00:26:40,732
Not right now.

455
00:26:41,153 --> 00:26:43,126
But I might cause
an accident in the future.

456
00:26:44,732 --> 00:26:45,570
Okay.

457
00:26:46,106 --> 00:26:49,686
I'll protect you and
your mom no matter what.

458
00:26:49,783 --> 00:26:50,509
Is that good?

459
00:26:53,141 --> 00:26:56,281
But are you really okay?
You don't look so well.

460
00:28:13,458 --> 00:28:14,466
Mom...

461
00:28:17,332 --> 00:28:18,029
Mom...

462
00:28:18,823 --> 00:28:20,897
-She's regaining her consciousness.
-Mom.

463
00:28:20,982 --> 00:28:22,416
She's waking up!

464
00:28:23,478 --> 00:28:25,108
Miss. Are you awake?

465
00:28:25,193 --> 00:28:28,087
Where's my mom right now?

466
00:28:31,481 --> 00:28:32,677
Yoobum...

467
00:28:35,374 --> 00:28:36,160
Hongjoo.

468
00:28:37,196 --> 00:28:39,101
Nam Hongjoo. Can you see?

469
00:28:39,610 --> 00:28:41,207
Can you see how many I'm holding up?

470
00:28:45,583 --> 00:28:46,538
Where's mom?

471
00:29:01,049 --> 00:29:01,940
My hair...

472
00:29:04,216 --> 00:29:05,430
Why is my hair...

473
00:29:10,102 --> 00:29:10,987
Aunt.

474
00:29:12,149 --> 00:29:13,304
What day is it today?

475
00:29:13,549 --> 00:29:14,474
Today?

476
00:29:15,726 --> 00:29:17,304
Today is Christmas Eve.

477
00:29:20,961 --> 00:29:24,396
Christmas has passed.

478
00:29:25,443 --> 00:29:26,950
And it's been three months.

479
00:29:27,042 --> 00:29:30,899
Miss. You were in
the hospital for 10 months.

480
00:29:34,729 --> 00:29:35,565
Aunt.

481
00:29:37,382 --> 00:29:38,420
Where's mom?

482
00:29:39,534 --> 00:29:40,775
Later...

483
00:29:42,366 --> 00:29:44,975
I'll tell you when you
come to your senses.

484
00:29:45,060 --> 00:29:46,609
I'm totally fine.

485
00:29:48,015 --> 00:29:49,054
Tell me right now.

486
00:29:53,883 --> 00:29:56,350
You should've woken up a little sooner.

487
00:29:56,977 --> 00:30:01,779
Your mom held on as best as
she could to see you wake up...

488
00:30:03,962 --> 00:30:05,770
What are you talking about?

489
00:30:07,767 --> 00:30:09,307
What happened to mom?

490
00:30:11,111 --> 00:30:13,411
Because of the accident you caused...

491
00:30:15,465 --> 00:30:17,756
...someone died.

492
00:30:18,883 --> 00:30:21,553
My son!

493
00:30:22,875 --> 00:30:26,024
Bring back my son!

494
00:30:30,982 --> 00:30:32,897
My baby...

495
00:30:33,600 --> 00:30:35,203
Please wake up.

496
00:30:35,428 --> 00:30:37,102
I'll make you delicious food.

497
00:30:37,961 --> 00:30:39,771
To come up with the settlement
money for the death...

498
00:30:40,248 --> 00:30:41,757
...the young man and your hospital bill...

499
00:30:42,215 --> 00:30:45,534
...your mom sold the house
and the restaurant.

500
00:30:45,988 --> 00:30:48,151
She worked day and night without rest.

501
00:30:50,334 --> 00:30:52,490
She wanted to save you...

502
00:30:53,149 --> 00:30:56,017
But due to over exhaustion...

503
00:31:15,182 --> 00:31:16,228
She passed away?

504
00:31:16,985 --> 00:31:18,257
Yes.

505
00:31:40,198 --> 00:31:43,416
"To my daughter, Hongjoo...
1 and 2. Cancel the fixed deposit."

506
00:31:43,516 --> 00:31:49,583
"3. Claim the life insurance.
4. Don't blame yourself."

507
00:31:52,716 --> 00:31:53,712
This is a dream.

508
00:31:55,649 --> 00:31:56,744
This is a dream, isn't it?

509
00:31:57,182 --> 00:31:58,826
Tell me that this is a dream.

510
00:32:02,649 --> 00:32:04,122
I have to wake up.

511
00:32:04,816 --> 00:32:06,291
Why can't I wake up?

512
00:32:09,687 --> 00:32:12,697
Please tell me that this is a dream.

513
00:32:13,840 --> 00:32:15,254
Hongjoo.

514
00:32:16,549 --> 00:32:17,901
I don't want to dream.

515
00:32:20,405 --> 00:32:21,472
Aunt.

516
00:32:23,037 --> 00:32:24,609
Come to your senses.

517
00:32:25,182 --> 00:32:27,349
You might have to go to court.

518
00:32:28,982 --> 00:32:30,248
What are you talking about?

519
00:32:31,052 --> 00:32:32,452
Why do I have to go to court?

520
00:32:33,384 --> 00:32:35,946
I didn't drive so why do I have to?

521
00:32:36,395 --> 00:32:37,741
You didn't drive?

522
00:32:38,350 --> 00:32:40,725
Why do you keep telling me
that I caused the accident?

523
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:42,594
I didn't drive.

524
00:32:42,878 --> 00:32:45,792
I didn't cause the accident.

525
00:32:51,203 --> 00:32:54,706
"Kiyoung Hospital"

526
00:32:55,649 --> 00:32:56,832
Suspect questioning...

527
00:32:57,085 --> 00:32:58,168
What's going on?

528
00:32:58,253 --> 00:33:01,096
You know that woman who
woke up after 10 months?

529
00:33:01,181 --> 00:33:03,089
She's being questioned here.

530
00:33:03,174 --> 00:33:04,249
At the hospital ward?

531
00:33:04,462 --> 00:33:05,550
They're here.

532
00:33:05,825 --> 00:33:07,352
I think that person is the prosecutor.

533
00:33:07,952 --> 00:33:09,688
-Are you the guardian?
-No.

534
00:33:22,164 --> 00:33:23,330
Miss Nam Hongjoo.

535
00:33:23,415 --> 00:33:25,471
Do you understand that you're
being questioned for violating...

536
00:33:25,556 --> 00:33:27,487
...the Special Case Concerning
Traffic Accident Act?

537
00:33:27,572 --> 00:33:29,459
You have the right to remain silent...

538
00:33:29,544 --> 00:33:32,524
...and refuse to answer any questions
that may be used against you.

539
00:33:32,697 --> 00:33:36,147
Refusing to answer questions
will not be used against you.

540
00:33:38,526 --> 00:33:39,551
Because it's me...

